Antwerpen 10 gb 1681
conffr in antwoort aenden ul van gisteren de lakens sijn nae londen
sal wegh gesonden & tgelt wort prompt voldaen wet voorseker dat
het aen mij niet en sal manqueren als wanneer ick aen ul broeders kam
dinst doen & mijn foute niet en is geweest dat het soo lanck heeft
gettardeert want ick altijt bereyt ben geweest & gebeden hebbe om
een eijnde te maken, lakende dat ul strijft dat mons. verspret de
penninge tot London soude hebbe gearresteert hebbe heden u broden
gesproken den welcken seght, als dat sulx soude sijn geschat pso -
forma, tot versekeringe van u broeders doch eijgenthijh en kan ick
de saeke niet ul broeder heeft gesejt selfs aen ul te scrgven tis
seker dat monsr. verspreet u broeders vrint is tgene hij doet maer
salleen is tot hun voordeel sal treken
Mons. Nicolaer Hengclair
monsr. En response a la vre du8 courant je vous remercie del honnour
que vous stuer donne a ma lettre a mons. trivier pour la Reste de
vre premiere courpt. les bayes dant ie vous ey escri sont arrive, et
je vous envoyerey plapre barque sur brussee amad devos 6 peeces selon
vre ordre de la melieur sorte et si bon marcke qui ie les peufaire
pour vous animer decontinuer ensemble en cortespondence pour
de crisette, ie confess quealors ie nestois pas for bien pour veu mais
I attend decour auttre un pertie laplus belle, qu'ie j'amais eu, et ie
vous envoyerey un deplus beau,et aussi ie vous laisserey rabatre
ce qu'il serett reasonable car lanne de plaire mes acis puis que le
quand il vous plaira devenit ie ne
suis avec mes besse
manquerey pas amon dbroor pour vous bien servir estant a present
fort bien proveuayant reeunirghres prandepertie de nouel marchand is
d 10 ditto 1681
mons. Bierre meurant
mons. En responce ala vre du y courant, j'attendu deiour aultre vre
responce a la miene du 31 passato, non obstante pour de carise dont vous
estrive ils sont arrive il y a 20 peeces dans les packs avec un baye
fardelure et ils sont de blancke lifte mais melieur, et plus large
qui les precedentens, ils me coustent 1o pater a la peeces plus si vous
les voulen laisse moy scavoir avec la preaultrement ies seront
vendu, aussi ne manque poun d'escrim touschant les & draps denont
presse dont ie vous ey envoyez les eschantillions, et les quelle vous
avez muse acoste, car ie les ey lasse a part & monpreuve cc ayet
en l'occasion de ses pouvoir vendre bief deux fois en attendent

London Will Scawen
S. my last to you was on the 5: curitt to which please to be referred
sence recd yd of 21: past with factury of the 10s salempores ma
bale IM„N.1 aboard van fenwish which is wel arrived att ostend
so exspect the goods heres towards next weck. nnot ron the rrestng
goods will be sold as neare as possible as also yd acctt: ready towards
ids arrivall here on which you may depend I have given vourreditt
for my halfe share in the above mentioned bale N.1 I desire no more
goods for this time much less th brouwn cloth att Lille, because
the charges should be to much & the less I have now the soones
all will becleared to begin on new towards next sale. & returne
you thanckes that you will be pleased tosels my packett N.3: as best
you can, which pay do, for Ill send no more for my acctt. exspectig
yd, answer for the packest N.4 which is herefill & so with vort
andr satusf kenneue
fntr: 12 gb 1681
London John Layd
th
S. mj last to you was on the 5: curitt sence recd. yd of 21: past, the artf
cortificatie is not yett don because our onely english notary had no
time yett to gohim self in to the casth, yett he promised to performe
before nextpost, so I shall not faile to send itt accordingly att beengne
trouble att all to mee when I can serve a freind & principally in matters of
charntie, in the meane while in thomas hartopp, one of this towne is
now in london & you may finde him, either by mr. Henry Collier or
mr. Lucy knightley, he hath beenvere much acquainted with m. more
alias norton, if the widdow could speake with him he would be able to
tell more then I shall cossibly, gett inpaper written for he hath osten
discoursed with him & knows severall of his passages, as Iam told, he
beeng vere compbasant I doubt not butt he will give you dor the eidon
full content as for bos yarne must be hale white, because of the winted
time butt towards march next & st brill itt may be half white or raw
or not whitened attall, so for the triall & because of the season itt
must now be all or hole white to serve presentley, and the parcells assorted
from 8 to 16 ounces the bos, I do not question butt in case you are
well served in the yearne, that you will finde vere good returnes in
tjkes & so that you will out do all & gett well. inclosed is anote of
100 tykes which cost 1o first penice the charges are not more now then
formerly to yd governo & do assure you that they be curious goods &
cheaper they can not be bought the 2 seales are foulded 2 mone
as also the great lead, so that will safe some thing in the charges
a goivrno, you shall have the soo weight of clovere seeds p. vere
first as to the nictures you can have butt here fo p. for 50 a ƒƒ60:
yett Ill do my endeavour as well I can butt please first to advise mee
how bigg or spuare they must be, for haveing there or there about y ds
measure shall be better able to serve you to content, you may send the
measure with a thread p yd next & I doubt not butt that I shall f inde sor
some thing to yd content whilst & remaine with kinde
pray do mee the favourtogett the inclosed accepted I llserve you n the likerid
@ 12 dito
lond- ney knightley
th
Sr. in answer to yd of 24: past, I'll do what I can for the disposing of yd kersies
butt I am sorry that I am notable to do any good swith . because ourpeople
knows not the sort areused to 22 yd & 30 yd which cost much less. I observe
that yd agie is returned which is not good principally this time a yeare
I have been in commoded bj bleeding which had almost carried mee awaj
if I had not been helped on asuddame, otherwyse such I have not been
although that bleeding weakned meemore then a great sichness as foryds
chargeng mee p. ex. all is well yett Ihope the good freind will give butt seldo
more that truble I take notice that you have 7 excellent redds of £10:10
of which I am glad because yd last bale is not yett sald all, which were so
bad & thread bade that they were att least 1o b inferior to formar goods
which made mee verely belevve that because of yd indisposition you
had not bought them yd selfs, nonsced y for & am confident you
should not have sent y Ihope you will not take itt that 2 spake my
minde butt do mee the favour to take 5 of theise best redds & gett
anvorees of £11 9 22, a £13 ap &2 bayes wrappers of about 40ss ap. send
them mee pr. first, & ill see you puintually satisfied which isall att present
@ 12 ditto
London Henry Collier
S. in answer to yds of 14 & 24: past: inclosed returne you mr. kart op plette
he hath not yett been att fom home sence to demand from him the charges
butt I doubt he shall not pay them neither yett herreynme will do his endeevous
I petty poore biclley ended forhe is not the cause of yd loss, I could wish he had
some imploy tolive forold & noore are 2 badd things: Iam told that yous
mr. Hurtopp is now in london beeng gon over with the last gaght & do
not question butt he well come to see you, so that there shall faile
noopportnitie to make yds complaints he is likely enough to be well
advanced here for is good behavonw, I was told that he is madea cap of fort
in the kiighs sermee here, which I should be gladd of to know to be so
